The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 December is 15,146 (1,753 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 December, there were 2,661 new confirmed cases (308.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 December, there were 1,456 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 83% (1,205 extra cases).
